{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature extraction is the simplest and most data-efficient form of transfer learning: a pretrained network is used as a fixed function that maps raw inputs to rich, general-purpose representations, and only a small new classifier trained on top of those representations is updated for the target task. Because the backbone's weights are frozen, even a few hundred labeled examples in the new domain can produce strong results."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Feature Extraction Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In the context of transfer learning, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "feature extraction"}, {"type": "text", "text": " means taking a deep network that was trained on a large dataset (the source domain) and using all but its final classification layer as a fixed "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "feature extractor"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Every input is passed forward through the frozen backbone to produce an embedding vector, and only a lightweight new head—typically one or two dense layers—is trained on the target dataset."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The two main scenarios are:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vision:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " A CNN pretrained on ImageNet (e.g., ResNet-50, EfficientNet) extracts spatial feature maps from an image; a global average-pooling step then collapses them to a single vector per image."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NLP:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " A transformer pretrained on large text (e.g., BERT, RoBERTa) produces contextual token embeddings; the [CLS] token embedding or a mean-pool of token embeddings is used as the sentence representation."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why It Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Deep networks trained on large, diverse datasets learn a hierarchy of general-purpose feature detectors. Early layers capture low-level patterns (edges, color gradients, n-gram statistics), and later layers compose those into higher-level abstractions (object parts, semantic relationships). These representations transfer because many real-world tasks share the same low-level and mid-level structure, even when the output labels differ entirely."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formally, let "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "f_{\\theta}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " denote the frozen backbone parameterized by "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\theta"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (fixed after pretraining). For a new input "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", the extracted feature vector is:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\phi(x) = f_{\\theta}(x), \\quad \\theta \\text{ fixed}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A new head "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "g_{\\phi}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " with trainable parameters "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\phi"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is then trained on the target dataset "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\{(x_i, y_i)\\}_{i=1}^{N}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " by minimizing:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\mathcal{L}(\\phi) = \\frac{1}{N} \\sum_{i=1}^{N} \\ell\\!\\left(g_{\\phi}(\\phi(x_i)),\\, y_i\\right)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Because "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\phi(x)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is precomputed and fixed, gradients flow only through "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "g_{\\phi}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", making training fast even on a CPU."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Architecture"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The diagram below shows the feature extraction pipeline: new-task data flows through the frozen backbone to produce a fixed-size embedding, which feeds into a small trainable head that produces predictions for the target classes."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Feature extraction transfer learning diagram: frozen backbone produces fixed embeddings; only the new classification head is trained"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data efficiency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Excellent performance with hundreds of examples, not millions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Features can be precomputed once; only a small head trains, often on CPU in seconds"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Low overfitting risk"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fewer trainable parameters means less chance of memorizing a small dataset"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No GPU required for training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Once embeddings are cached, a logistic regression or shallow MLP trains on standard hardware"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stable training"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Frozen weights eliminate risk of catastrophic forgetting or unstable backbone gradients"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Domain mismatch ceiling"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If the target domain differs sharply from the source (e.g., medical scans vs. natural photos), frozen features may be suboptimal; fine-tuning gives better results"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fixed representation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The backbone cannot adapt its features to task-specific patterns; fine-tuning can squeeze out additional performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inference cost unchanged"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serving still runs the full backbone; no parameter reduction at inference time"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cache storage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Precomputing and storing embeddings for large datasets requires significant disk space"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How It Works"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The mechanics follow three stages:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Obtain a pretrained backbone."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Load a model trained on a large source dataset (ImageNet, C4 text corpus, etc.). The backbone excludes the final classification head."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Freeze backbone weights."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Set "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\texttt{requires\\_grad = False}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for every backbone parameter. This prevents any gradient update from propagating into the pretrained layers."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Extract and cache embeddings (optional but recommended)."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Pass all target-domain inputs through the frozen backbone once and save the resulting vectors. Subsequent training epochs operate on the cached vectors, not on raw inputs, which is orders of magnitude faster."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Train the new head."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Attach a small MLP (or a single linear layer for simple tasks) and train it on the cached embeddings with standard supervised learning."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Feature Extraction"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Condition"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Recommendation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small target dataset (< ~2 000 examples)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature extraction preferred"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Target domain similar to source domain"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature extraction preferred"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited compute budget (CPU only, fast iteration)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature extraction preferred"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large target dataset (> ~10 000 examples)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fine-tuning likely better"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Target domain differs significantly from source"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fine-tuning (or pretraining from scratch)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Implement"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vision — PyTorch with torchvision"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\nfrom torchvision import models, transforms\nfrom torch.utils.data import DataLoader, TensorDataset\n\n# 1. Load pretrained backbone, drop its classifier\nbackbone = models.resnet50(weights=models.ResNet50_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V2)\nbackbone.fc = nn.Identity()  # remove the 1000-class head\nbackbone.eval()              # inference mode — no dropout / batchnorm tracking\n\n# Freeze every backbone parameter\nfor param in backbone.parameters():\n    param.requires_grad = False\n\n# 2. Precompute embeddings (run once)\ntransform = transforms.Compose([\n    transforms.Resize(256),\n    transforms.CenterCrop(224),\n    transforms.ToTensor(),\n    transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406],\n                         std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225]),\n])\n\ndevice = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\nbackbone = backbone.to(device)\n\nall_embeds, all_labels = [], []\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    for images, labels in train_loader:          # your DataLoader\n        embeds = backbone(images.to(device))     # shape (B, 2048)\n        all_embeds.append(embeds.cpu())\n        all_labels.append(labels)\n\nX_train = torch.cat(all_embeds)   # (N, 2048)\ny_train = torch.cat(all_labels)   # (N,)\n\n# 3. Train a small head on the cached embeddings\nhead = nn.Sequential(\n    nn.Linear(2048, 256),\n    nn.ReLU(),\n    nn.Dropout(0.3),\n    nn.Linear(256, num_classes),   # your number of target classes\n)\n\noptimizer = torch.optim.Adam(head.parameters(), lr=1e-3)\nloss_fn   = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n\nembed_loader = DataLoader(\n    TensorDataset(X_train, y_train), batch_size=256, shuffle=True\n)\n\nfor epoch in range(30):\n    for x_batch, y_batch in embed_loader:\n        logits = head(x_batch)\n        loss = loss_fn(logits, y_batch)\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        loss.backward()\n        optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NLP — HuggingFace Transformers"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModel\nimport torch\nimport torch.nn as nn\n\nMODEL_NAME = \"bert-base-uncased\"\n\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\nencoder   = AutoModel.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\n\n# Freeze the entire BERT backbone\nfor param in encoder.parameters():\n    param.requires_grad = False\n\n# Helper: mean-pool token embeddings (ignores padding)\ndef mean_pool(model_output, attention_mask):\n    token_embeds = model_output.last_hidden_state          # (B, T, 768)\n    mask = attention_mask.unsqueeze(-1).float()            # (B, T, 1)\n    return (token_embeds * mask).sum(1) / mask.sum(1)     # (B, 768)\n\n# Precompute sentence embeddings\nencoder.eval()\ndevice = torch.device(\"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\")\nencoder = encoder.to(device)\n\nall_embeds, all_labels = [], []\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    for sentences, labels in train_loader:\n        enc = tokenizer(sentences, padding=True, truncation=True,\n                        max_length=128, return_tensors=\"pt\").to(device)\n        out = encoder(**enc)\n        embeds = mean_pool(out, enc[\"attention_mask\"])   # (B, 768)\n        all_embeds.append(embeds.cpu())\n        all_labels.append(labels)\n\nX_train = torch.cat(all_embeds)\ny_train = torch.cat(all_labels)\n\n# Train a linear classifier on the embeddings\nclassifier = nn.Linear(768, num_classes)\noptimizer  = torch.optim.AdamW(classifier.parameters(), lr=2e-4)\nloss_fn    = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n\nfor epoch in range(20):\n    perm = torch.randperm(len(X_train))\n    for i in range(0, len(X_train), 64):\n        idx = perm[i:i+64]\n        logits = classifier(X_train[idx])\n        loss = loss_fn(logits, y_train[idx])\n        optimizer.zero_grad()\n        loss.backward()\n        optimizer.step()"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature Extraction vs. Fine-Tuning"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature Extraction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fine-Tuning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backbone gradients"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "None (frozen)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Full or partial"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data needed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very small (100s – low 1000s)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate to large (1 000s – 100 000s)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training time"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Seconds to minutes (head only)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minutes to hours (full network)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Overfitting risk"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Higher (needs regularization)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Peak accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good, especially in-domain"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Highest across most tasks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Catastrophic forgetting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Not possible"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Risk if learning rate too high"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Real-World Example"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A radiology startup needs to classify chest X-rays into 10 pathology classes. They have 1 200 labeled images — far too few to train a CNN from scratch on image sizes exceeding 512×512. Their approach:"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Load a DenseNet-121 pretrained on CheXpert (a large chest X-ray dataset) — an even better source domain than ImageNet."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Freeze all convolutional blocks. Run all 1 200 images through the frozen network once (~15 minutes on CPU) and cache 1 024-dimensional embedding vectors."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Train a two-layer MLP on the cached vectors for 50 epochs — total time under 30 seconds on CPU."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Achieve 82% macro-F1 on the held-out test set. A ResNet-50 trained from scratch on the same 1 200 images achieves only 61% macro-F1."}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Because the source and target domains are both chest X-rays, the pretrained features transfer almost perfectly, and the data constraint makes feature extraction clearly the right choice over fine-tuning."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Mistakes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forgetting to call model.eval()."}, {"type": "text", "text": " BatchNorm layers in the backbone use running statistics in eval mode. Leaving the backbone in training mode lets batch statistics shift the embeddings inconsistently across batches, producing noisy features."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not matching preprocessing to the pretrained model."}, {"type": "text", "text": " ImageNet pretrained models expect inputs normalized to the ImageNet mean and standard deviation. Using different normalization degrades embedding quality significantly."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Extracting from the wrong layer."}, {"type": "text", "text": " For most tasks, the penultimate layer (before the final classifier) gives the best features. Using an earlier intermediate layer loses high-level semantic information; using the original final softmax loses transferability."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Applying feature extraction when the domain gap is large."}, {"type": "text", "text": " An ImageNet backbone used on satellite imagery or molecular graphs will produce poor features because the source-domain patterns do not generalize. In such cases, domain-adaptive pretraining or fine-tuning is needed."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training the head with too high a learning rate."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Even though the backbone is frozen, an excessively high learning rate on the small head causes it to overfit on embedding artifacts rather than task structure."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best Practices"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cache embeddings to disk."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Precomputing and saving embeddings with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "torch.save"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or NumPy eliminates backbone inference overhead during each training epoch. For a dataset of 10 000 images, this turns multi-minute epochs into sub-second ones."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Normalize embeddings."}, {"type": "text", "text": " L2-normalizing the feature vectors before training the head often improves convergence and final accuracy, especially for cosine-distance-sensitive tasks such as retrieval."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Start with a linear probe."}, {"type": "text", "text": " A single linear layer on top of the frozen embeddings is a strong baseline and provides a lower bound. Only add non-linearity if the linear probe plateaus."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use data augmentation only at extraction time."}, {"type": "text", "text": " If the dataset is very small, run the feature extractor on multiple augmented views of each image, producing several embedding vectors per sample. This effectively multiplies the training set without adding labels."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Validate domain similarity before committing."}, {"type": "text", "text": " Compute the cosine similarity between source-domain and target-domain embedding distributions (e.g., mean-pool a sample from each). High similarity confirms feature extraction will transfer well; low similarity suggests fine-tuning."}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of the pretrained backbone as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "universal translator for raw perception"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". It was trained for years on enormous data to understand the structure of the world — edges, shapes, grammar, semantics. Feature extraction asks this translator to read new inputs and produce a description in its learned language (the embedding). A small new classifier then learns, in that rich language, what constitutes class A versus class B. The translator itself never changes; only the lightweight \"dictionary\" mapping the translated descriptions to new labels is updated."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Feature extraction freezes the pretrained backbone entirely and trains only a new lightweight head, making it the most data- and compute-efficient form of transfer learning."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "It works because deep networks learn general hierarchical representations that transfer across tasks when the source and target domains share low- to mid-level structure."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Caching embeddings before training the head eliminates repeated backbone inference, reducing wall-clock training time from minutes to seconds."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The key implementation requirement is setting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "requires_grad = False"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on all backbone parameters and calling "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "model.eval()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " before extraction."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prefer feature extraction when the target dataset is small (under ~2 000 examples) or the budget is constrained; switch to fine-tuning when data is abundant or the domain gap is large."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes — wrong normalization, wrong extraction layer, and leaving the backbone in training mode — each independently degrade embedding quality and should be checked systematically."}]}]}]}]}}